  <main>
    <section id="what-is-html5">
      <h2>What is HTML5?</h2>
      <p>HTML5 is the latest version of the Hypertext Markup Language. It introduces semantic tags that improve content structure and provide meaning to web documents.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="accessibility">
      <h2>Accessibility</h2>
      <article>
        <h3>Making the Web Inclusive</h3>
        <p>Accessibility ensures that websites are usable by everyone, including people with disabilities. Semantic HTML5 helps screen readers and other assistive technologies understand web content.</p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Best Practices</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Use semantic landmarks like <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code>.</li>
          <li>Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible.</li>
          <li>Provide descriptive titles, alt text, and link labels.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="seo">
      <h2>SEO Basics</h2>
      <p>Search Engine Optimization (SEO) helps your site appear in search engine results. Using proper HTML structure and descriptive content helps search engines understand your page.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use clear and logical heading hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3).</li>
        <li>Include relevant keywords in headings and paragraphs.</li>
        <li>Add a meta description to describe your page content.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>

